I'm worried about the river, we swim.

783
01:04:05,239 --> 01:04:06,240
You never know, sir.

784
01:04:32,678 --> 01:04:35,930
I have, of course,
looked everywhere here already.

785
01:04:57,198 --> 01:04:58,698
Everything you do...

786
01:04:59,574 --> 01:05:02,160
...everything you say, write...

787
01:05:04,079 --> 01:05:05,664
...you do it superbly.

788
01:05:06,873 --> 01:05:09,124
And you're always going to, all your life...

789
01:05:09,375 --> 01:05:11,125
...whatever you turn your hand to. I know it.

790
01:05:14,585 --> 01:05:17,922
And I know you must feel
that I don't belong in your world.

791
01:05:19,090 --> 01:05:22,051
I don't.

792
01:06:22,018 --> 01:06:23,267
Between the soup and the baked beans.

793
01:06:24,018 --> 01:06:25,561
Thank you so much.

794
01:06:26,020 --> 01:06:28,022
I caught her before she got to the check-out.

795
01:06:28,522 --> 01:06:30,316
She's been gone for hours...

796
01:06:30,524 --> 01:06:31,650
..I thought I'd never see her again. Never.

797
01:06:33,318 --> 01:06:34,694
Well... all's well that...

798
01:06:35,069 --> 01:06:36,945
Please do, tell me your name?

799
01:06:39,822 --> 01:06:41,282
I'm Maurice, John.

800
01:06:43,701 --> 01:06:44,827
Iris' friend.

801
01:06:45,994 --> 01:06:47,829
I was a witness at your wedding.

802
01:06:50,457 --> 01:06:51,999
Well, I'm late for a meeting.

803
01:06:52,708 --> 01:06:56,169
-Maurice, so sorry...
-So sorry.

804
01:07:28,322 --> 01:07:30,823
Were you trying to get away from me?

805
01:07:32,658 --> 01:07:35,576
Did you want to leave me, Iris?

806
01:07:38,078 --> 01:07:39,746
Please?

807
01:07:54,968 --> 01:07:57,928
I feel as if I don't know anything about you.

808
01:07:58,262 --> 01:07:59,513
When you know
everything about me, then I'll be dead.

809
01:08:00,472 --> 01:08:01,765
He's a Professor of Ancient History..

810
01:08:02,224 --> 01:08:04,058
They have a maling influence on you I think.

811
01:08:04,308 --> 01:08:05,518
They all have, all your 'friends'.

812
01:08:05,892 --> 01:08:07,936
He's a teacher, a master of thought.

813
01:08:08,561 --> 01:08:10,729
You talk, do you. You master thoughts together?

814
01:08:11,397 --> 01:08:13,482
We make love, yes,
but that's not the important thing.

815
01:08:13,774 --> 01:08:15,150
Then he goes home to his wife in London.

816
01:08:15,943 --> 01:08:16,902
Does it frighten you?

817
01:08:17,444 --> 01:08:20,862
I feel as if I'm standing in a long line of suitors...

818
01:08:21,071 --> 01:08:22,239
...waiting for a kind word.

819
01:08:23,115 --> 01:08:24,157
I'll always give you a kind word.

820
01:08:25,242 --> 01:08:26,702
We must accept me as I am.

821
01:08:27,494 --> 01:08:29,663
And I'm to be kept in my box or not kept at all.

822
01:08:30,122 --> 01:08:32,915
Nothing matters except...

823
01:08:34,125 --> 01:08:35,417
...loving what is good.

824
01:08:35,875 --> 01:08:36,876
Am I good?

825
01:08:39,336 --> 01:08:41,213
Just...

826
01:08:41,505 --> 01:08:44,215
...keep tight hold of me and it'll be all right.

827
01:08:50,637 --> 01:08:53,140
Who are you with now, Iris?

828
01:08:53,140 --> 01:08:54,141
Who is it?

829
01:08:59,520 --> 01:09:03,107
We're lost.

830
01:09:04,483 --> 01:09:06,651
We're lost. We're lost...

831
01:09:16,658 --> 01:09:17,993
There is no reason for this.

832
01:09:18,327 --> 01:09:19,953
And if there is I don't know it.

833
01:09:20,871 --> 01:09:24,207
I hate you Iris. You stupid cow.

834
01:09:24,625 --> 01:09:26,043
I bloody loathe you.

835
01:09:26,335 --> 01:09:28,461
Every bloody inch of you.

836
01:09:29,003 --> 01:09:31,670
All your friends have finished with you.

837
01:09:32,087 --> 01:09:34,881
Nobody else has you anymore...

838
01:09:35,381 --> 01:09:40,053
...except your fucking best friend
Doctor fucking Alzheimer....

839
01:09:40,428 --> 01:09:43,056
...with all his fucking gifts.

840
01:09:43,514 --> 01:09:46,642
I've got you now and I don't want you.

841
01:09:47,935 --> 01:09:50,186
I've never known anything about you at all...

842
01:09:50,519 --> 01:09:51,979
...and now I don't care.

843
01:10:01,696 --> 01:10:02,780
I think it's time I told you about...

844
01:10:02,905 --> 01:10:03,906
...some of my friends...

845
01:10:04,989 --> 01:10:07,450
...the people in my past -- of my heart and...

846
01:10:08,326 --> 01:10:09,284
...and not.

847
01:10:11,870 --> 01:10:12,829
Oh dear.

848
01:10:20,335 --> 01:10:21,753
ought I to take notes?

849
01:10:29,593 --> 01:10:31,512
There was a friend who was a student with me.

850
01:10:33,763 --> 01:10:35,348
No, no, he can wait.

851
01:10:37,975 --> 01:10:39,977
He was not the first person I went to bed with...

852
01:10:40,852 --> 01:10:42,020
...that was Harry..

853
01:10:43,396 --> 01:10:46,023
then there was Roger,
who wanted to marry me...

854
01:10:46,857 --> 01:10:49,401
And Oscar
who said he couldn't live without me...

855
01:10:50,735 --> 01:10:52,237
...and Tom...

856
01:10:53,779 --> 01:10:58,033
...who far too clearly could but...

857
01:10:58,367 --> 01:11:01,328
So, the student friend
I had resisted going to bed with...

858
01:11:03,204 --> 01:11:04,581
...joined the Army during the war....

859
01:11:04,914 --> 01:11:06,040
...and promptly asked me to marry him for...

860
01:11:07,875 --> 01:11:09,500
...he was certain he was going to be killed...

861
01:11:09,791 --> 01:11:11,167
..and wanted me to have the window's pension.

862
01:11:13,086 --> 01:11:14,379
Yes, I know they all said that.

863
01:11:16,047 --> 01:11:17,007
Anyway...

864
01:11:18,967 --> 01:11:20,385
...I didn't want to marry him...

865
01:11:22,387 --> 01:11:24,139
...but I did go to bed with him.

866
01:11:24,764 --> 01:11:29,017
...I thought that best before
he went off to fight, because you never know...

867
01:11:34,437 --> 01:11:36,147
...anyway, he, he was killed--

868
01:11:36,939 --> 01:11:38,316
--my student friend...

869
01:11:40,151 --> 01:11:41,569
...and we weren't married.

870
01:11:44,279 --> 01:11:45,530
So no pension.

871
01:11:53,828 --> 01:11:54,829
there.

872
01:11:55,038 --> 01:11:56,122
It wouldn't have been much anyway...

873
01:11:56,331 --> 01:11:57,749
I know, because I had friends killed.

874
01:11:58,082 --> 01:12:00,292
Their wives got very little, they get very little.

875
01:12:05,087 --> 01:12:07,422
Is that all? I mean, roughly?

876
01:12:09,716 --> 01:12:11,927
What about the 'friends' in your other world?

877
01:12:13,261 --> 01:12:14,721
You know more about me than anyone on earth.

878
01:12:19,057 --> 01:12:20,266
You are my world.

879
01:12:42,743 --> 01:12:43,744
Thank you.

880
01:12:45,496 --> 01:12:47,664
After all that I rather hoped it might be time...

881
01:12:47,997 --> 01:12:49,290
...for me to get my kind word.

882
01:12:56,004 --> 01:12:58,465
You don't need to do it on your own.
Vale House is very good.

883
01:12:59,424 --> 01:13:00,801
You're exhausted, you know that.

884
01:13:01,176 --> 01:13:03,135
Of course I am. It's something that we share.

885
01:13:03,511 --> 01:13:05,762
We're in a state of grace.

886
01:13:06,346 --> 01:13:07,971
I think we understand each other.

887
01:13:09,055 --> 01:13:10,098
What do you think?

888
01:13:11,140 --> 01:13:15,436
I don'tknow. There's always help if you need it.

889
01:13:16,604 --> 01:13:19,315
There isn't any help for her.

890
01:13:22,735 --> 01:13:23,736
What?

891
01:13:24,529 --> 01:13:26,487
Sorry? Sorry?

892
01:13:27,071 --> 01:13:28,280
Nothing.

893
01:13:37,621 --> 01:13:38,622
Why has Willie Thorne
got two rabbits tattooed on his bald head?

894
01:13:39,456 --> 01:13:41,958
I don't know, why has Willie Thorne
got two rabbits tattooed on his bald head?

895
01:13:42,542 --> 01:13:44,836
Cos from a distance they look like hares.

896
01:13:49,381 --> 01:13:50,591
Janet's dead, Iris.

897
01:13:55,595 --> 01:13:58,055
They want me to say a few words
but I can't think of any.

898
01:13:58,598 --> 01:14:00,973
Janet's dead, Iris.

899
01:14:11,733 --> 01:14:15,278
I miss Janet very much.

900
01:14:16,402 --> 01:14:20,823
I miss Janet because I used to store up...

901
01:14:21,240 --> 01:14:23,284
...funny things to tell her that happened to us.

902
01:14:25,244 --> 01:14:27,162
...things I can no longer tell Iris.

903
01:14:28,830 --> 01:14:31,040
Another friend visited us...

904
01:14:31,332 --> 01:14:32,499
...in Oxford overnight recently....

905
01:14:33,249 --> 01:14:35,502
...and I found her cleaning the bath.

906
01:14:36,753 --> 01:14:38,880
I said, "Oh, please, there's no need".

907
01:14:39,838 --> 01:14:41,924
She said, "Oh yes there is,
I want to take a bath".

908
01:14:47,053 --> 01:14:48,513
I was hoping to be able...

909
01:14:49,721 --> 01:14:51,056
...to tell Janet that story...

910
01:14:51,765 --> 01:14:53,808
...she would have enjoyed it.

911
01:14:54,851 --> 01:14:56,895
She would have...laughed.

912
01:14:59,523 --> 01:15:00,564
I mean, I think...

913
01:15:06,151 --> 01:15:09,237
...Anna Karenina, Tolstoy, you know...

914
01:15:09,529 --> 01:15:13,282
...when on her way to the station
to throw herself under a train...

915
01:15:14,200 --> 01:15:16,744
...sees something funny
which she thinks to tell Vronsky....

916
01:15:17,245 --> 01:15:18,204
...her lover, about...

917
01:15:18,788 --> 01:15:20,706
...we all do it, I do it with Iris...

918
01:15:21,040 --> 01:15:22,083
...and Janet, all our friends...

919
01:15:23,500 --> 01:15:28,503
...but, then Anna thought that
she wouldn't be seeing Vronsky again...

920
01:15:29,128 --> 01:15:31,338
...because she was about to kill herself.

921
01:15:35,843 --> 01:15:36,927
Oh, but, you don't want to hear this...

922
01:15:40,013 --> 01:15:42,306
...Janet didn't kill herself...

923
01:15:46,643 --> 01:15:51,021
But, if there's one thing
that would have prevented...

924
01:15:52,022 --> 01:15:54,942
...Anna from throwing herself under a train...

925
01:15:55,776 --> 01:16:00,696
...that would be it,
the thought of telling something funny...

926
01:16:02,364 --> 01:16:04,365
...to the man she loves.

927
01:16:08,536 --> 01:16:10,288
The love is over...

928
01:16:14,498 --> 01:16:17,877
...though...

929
01:16:20,171 --> 01:16:21,839
...life will...

930
01:16:23,299 --> 01:16:24,883
...soon be over.

931
01:16:27,302 --> 01:16:28,261
That's all.

932
01:16:30,220 --> 01:16:32,263
Goodbye, Janet.

933
01:16:32,805 --> 01:16:34,807
No, no, Janet. Jan!

934
01:16:35,516 --> 01:16:37,268
It's all right, Iris.

935
01:16:49,027 --> 01:16:49,986
Wrong, wrong, wrong.

936
01:16:50,236 --> 01:16:51,529
-Wrong driving.
Stop it, Iris!

937
01:16:51,905 --> 01:16:52,906
Wrong driving!

938
01:16:53,031 --> 01:16:54,032
No. Stop it, Iris.

939
01:16:54,365 --> 01:16:58,327
-Not house. Not mother..
-Iris, it's very dangerous.

940
01:16:58,619 --> 01:17:02,288
Them! Them!

941
01:17:05,039 --> 01:17:06,040
Iris!

942
01:17:12,880 --> 01:17:13,839
Puss.

943
01:17:16,091 --> 01:17:18,844
My old mouse -- My old cat mouse.

944
01:17:19,428 --> 01:17:20,429
Where are you?

945
01:17:48,576 --> 01:17:50,494
I...

946
01:17:53,455 --> 01:17:55,249
...love...

947
01:17:57,208 --> 01:17:58,333
...you.

948
01:18:00,377 --> 01:18:06,340
Ah, little mouse. I know you do.

949
01:18:21,728 --> 01:18:23,062
I used to be...

950
01:18:23,938 --> 01:18:26,566
...so afraid of being alone with you...

951
01:18:27,315 --> 01:18:29,025
...now I can't be without you.

952
01:18:38,825 --> 01:18:40,910
Let's get us -- home...

953
01:18:42,161 --> 01:18:44,455
...and then there'll be tomorrow...

954
01:18:46,289 --> 01:18:47,957
...and the nex tday...

955
01:18:49,292 --> 01:18:50,376
...and the next...

956
01:18:51,127 --> 01:18:52,462
...and on we go...

957
01:18:54,797 --> 01:18:59,092
...getting closer and closest together...

958
01:19:01,718 --> 01:19:02,719
Oh, your ring.

959
01:19:04,011 --> 01:19:05,471
It's so worn now.

960
01:19:05,804 --> 01:19:06,763
Where did you get it?

961
01:19:06,972 --> 01:19:07,973
From a pawnbrokers.

962
01:19:09,641 --> 01:19:11,018
I like things that are worn down.

963
01:19:13,061 --> 01:19:15,314
Which wear and wear and wear...

964
01:19:18,442 --> 01:19:19,735
...until they go.

965
01:19:37,748 --> 01:19:38,832
We've had a bit of luck.

966
01:19:39,792 --> 01:19:41,876
Usual thing, I'm afraid -- Somebody's died.

967
01:19:44,378 --> 01:19:45,379
Iris...

968
01:19:46,172 --> 01:19:49,174
...don't you have a smile for Doctor Gudgeon?

969
01:19:50,342 --> 01:19:51,301
No?

970
01:19:54,762 --> 01:19:55,763
No.

971
01:19:56,346 --> 01:19:58,890
So -- the time has come.

972
01:20:01,850 --> 01:20:03,268
You know it would, Professor Bayley.

973
01:20:04,103 --> 01:20:05,104
Yes.

974
01:20:06,021 --> 01:20:08,649
She didn't have a smile for you today.

975
01:20:09,316 --> 01:20:12,484
Yes. Well, we must make a start.

976
01:20:14,027 --> 01:20:15,821
-What do I do?
-Nothing any more.

977
01:20:19,533 --> 01:20:21,534
Vale House is a very friendly place, you know.

978
01:20:23,077 --> 01:20:24,328
I was, surpr....

979
01:20:26,204 --> 01:20:27,538
...I mean, this is one of the best.

980
01:20:30,290 --> 01:20:33,502
More difficult to get into than...well, Eton.

981
01:21:14,661 --> 01:21:16,746
-Taxi for Vale House?
-Yes.

982
01:21:18,456 --> 01:21:20,498
Lady's on the stairs, but I can't get her down.

983
01:21:22,249 --> 01:21:23,208
Shall I?

984
01:21:29,756 --> 01:21:32,300
You all right, my love?

985
01:21:34,552 --> 01:21:35,886
We're going for a little drive.

986
01:21:38,472 --> 01:21:39,472
What's your name then?

987
01:21:44,518 --> 01:21:45,518
Iris.

988
01:21:47,854 --> 01:21:49,647
Yes, it's Iris.

989
01:21:50,940 --> 01:21:51,983
All right then, Iris...

990
01:21:53,025 --> 01:21:54,567
...you'll be all right, my love, come on.

991
01:21:54,609 --> 01:21:55,610
Come on, upsy-daisy.

992
01:22:02,365 --> 01:22:03,366
There you go.

993
01:22:04,076 --> 01:22:05,911
Lovely.

994
01:22:32,890 --> 01:22:34,433
Human beings love each...

995
01:22:35,226 --> 01:22:37,144
...in sex -- in friendship...

996
01:22:38,020 --> 01:22:39,771
...and when they're in love.

997
01:22:41,147 --> 01:22:42,898
And they cherish other beings...

998
01:22:43,649 --> 01:22:46,693
...humans -- animals, plants...

999
01:22:48,487 --> 01:22:49,696
...even stones.

1000
01:22:50,447 --> 01:22:52,491
She'll be fine now, won't you Iris?

1001
01:22:55,159 --> 01:22:56,868
You can visit any time you like...

1002
01:22:57,244 --> 01:22:58,619
...come all day if you want to.

1003
01:23:03,832 --> 01:23:05,500
Stay the night, that's all right...

1004
01:23:06,126 --> 01:23:08,294
...we can make arrangements
for you to do that anytime.

1005
01:24:04,215 --> 01:24:06,092
It was so quiet...

1006
01:24:09,260 --> 01:24:10,386
...when she died.

1007
01:24:13,181 --> 01:24:16,976
Do you know,
I thought I wouldn't mind doing that myself..

1008
01:24:19,686 --> 01:24:22,938
I had a joke to tell her.

1009
01:24:25,523 --> 01:24:29,569
It wasn't a very good one
but she'd have laughed.

1010
01:24:31,070 --> 01:24:32,780
We need to believe in something divine.

1011
01:24:33,572 --> 01:24:34,823
Without the need for God.

1012
01:24:36,366 --> 01:24:38,951
Something we might call love...

1013
01:24:39,452 --> 01:24:40,453
...or goodness.

1014
01:24:41,912 --> 01:24:43,038
As the psalm says...

1015
01:24:44,289 --> 01:24:46,041
..."Whither shall I go from thy spirit...

1016
01:24:47,042 --> 01:24:48,752
...whither shall I flee from thy presence?

1017
01:24:50,504 --> 01:24:52,546
If I ascend unto Heaven thou art there...

1018
01:24:53,589 --> 01:24:56,341
...if I make my bed in Hell behold thou art there.

1019
01:24:58,050 --> 01:24:59,634
If I take the wings of the morning...

1020
01:25:00,093 --> 01:25:01,803
...and dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea...

1021
01:25:03,346 --> 01:25:05,390
...even there shall thy hand lead me...

1022
01:25:06,516 --> 01:25:08,476
...and thy right hand shall hold me."

